Ans: ZERO

If there are traffic lights in any Sunshine State, it is probably keeping a McDonald's restaurant occupied inside or outside of USA. I'm betting everything possible that Seychelles just simply doesn't understand what traffic lights mean. Frankly, they don't really care.

So let's imagine that my captaincy egocentricity instincts have kicked in. Let's say, for some (un)forseeable reason, I went to see a traffic light. What do you think the most crowded road in Seychelles deems to be like?

Ans: DEAD EMPTY

Have you seen any of the movies made by Quentin Tarantino? The last one which perhaps presumed the mass-casualty and pandemic of the most deadly style perhaps showed the Sawtooth intersection in Las Vegas. But my point is that nothing on this entire earth can compete with what I have experienced with last week in the streets of Seychelles.
